hedgehogs as pets are they good to have as a pet i think they are cute and am thinking about getting one anyone have any experience with them they can be great pets if you are the right owner for them my daughter has one and does very well with it we also have boys and worried the littlest two would let something like a hamster escape our hedgie is just intimidating enough that they don't get her out without help they aren't nocturnal but are diurnal so they are up some in the day mostly night though they need a wheel homemade bucket wheels are best and adequate space about sq feet min they can be sweet charming and addictive pets be forewarned though for such a small animal hedgehogs poop a lot on the other hand though since they are not a rodent they don't have much body odor at all keep the cage nice and clean and you don't have much smell feel free to email me Hamster Fancy rat Guinea pig Nocturnal animal Pet Cat Chinchilla Dog Sonic the Hedgehog Doctor Eggman Pet Sounds SpongeBob SquarePants Social rule Codename: Kids Next Door Ferret Domestic rabbit Sin City Yoko Ono Degu Internet phenomenon Phoebe Buffay's songs Shadow the Hedgehog (video game) Thermoregulation Skunk Pet skunk Hedgehog The Beach Boys Shaggy dog story Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog House Mouse Sense Coconut crab Pet store RuneScape quests Humphrey Bogart The Pet Sounds Sessions Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Kevin and Kell Spotted Skunk Shadow the Hedgehog W.I.T.C.H. Dream Garfield Rabbit AFI 100 Years series Tattoo Monster Rancher monsters The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie One Piece minor characters The McGuire Sisters Yu-Gi-Oh! anime, manga or movie only characters Kodocha The Amazing Maurice and his Educated Rodents Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Brown Rat Stoat Knots Landing Eric Cartman Negima Vulcan (Star Trek) STS-58 Aladdin (1992 film) Pet Sematary The Lovely Bones Anxiety Okashina Okashi Stop Huntingdon Animal Cruelty Kender Ron and Fez Sister Princess The